<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="149" type="remarks">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="149">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="149">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Y. C. Dai &amp; Chao G. Wang" authorityYear="2021" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Polyporaceae" genus="Bjerkandera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Bjerkandera fulgida" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="fulgida">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">Bjerkandera fulgida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is characterised by the resupinate to effused-reflexed basidiomata, clay buff to pale brown and shiny pore surface, and ellipsoid to broadly ellipsoid basidiospores measuring 3.9-4.5 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
2.8-3.3 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
. Phylogenetically, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Y. C. Dai &amp; Chao G. Wang" authorityYear="2021" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Polyporaceae" genus="Bjerkandera" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="Bjerkandera resupinata" order="Agaricales" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="resupinata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">Bjerkandera resupinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
nests in a sister clade to 
<taxonomicName class="Agaricomycetes" genus="B." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="B. fulgida" order="Polyporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="fulgida">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">B. fulgida</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figure 1. Phylogeny of Bjerkandera and related species generated by maximum parsimony analysis, based on combined ITS and nLSU sequences. Bootstrap support for maximum parsimony (MP), maximum likelihood (ML), and Bayesian posterior probabilities: (BPP) ≥ 50 % (MP-BT), 50 % (ML-BS) and 0.90 (BPP) are given in relation to the branches." figureDoi="10.3897/mycokeys.79.63908.figure1" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/536349" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">1</figureCitation>
), also having morphological similarities, as the pore surface coloration and presence of branched hyphae in the tubes. However, 
<taxonomicName class="Agaricomycetes" genus="B." higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Fungi" lsidName="B. resupinata" order="Polyporales" pageId="0" pageNumber="149" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="resupinata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="149">B. resupinata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs in having resupinate basidiomata, larger pores (4-6 per mm), and basidiospores measuring 4.5-6 
<normalizedToken originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
3.2-4.1 
<normalizedToken originalValue="μm">μm</normalizedToken>
.
</paragraph>
